<topic id="grid-start-editing">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="Steven" timestamp="20170525T111443+0300" comment="Merged into &quot;grid-actions.dita&quot;."?>Editing
    a Cell Value<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Grid editing mode<indexterm>Edit cell value</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Grid Mode editing<indexterm>Edit cell
            value</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Edit cell value in Grid Mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To edit the value of a cell, simply select the grid cell and press
          <uicontrol><shortcut>(Enter)</shortcut></uicontrol><ph product="author developer editor">
        or you can use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/StartEditing16.gif" id="image_eyj_33f_wr"
          /> Start Editing</uicontrol> action found in the <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Grid Edit</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu</ph>.</p>
    <p>To stop editing a cell value, press <uicontrol><shortcut>(Enter)</shortcut></uicontrol>
        again<ph product="author developer editor"> or use the <uicontrol><image
            href="../img/StopEditing16.gif" id="image_j4h_h3f_wr"/> End Editing</uicontrol> action
        found in the <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Grid Edit</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu</ph>.</p>
    <p>To cancel the editing without saving the current changes in the document, press the
          <uicontrol><shortcut>(Esc)</shortcut></uicontrol> key.</p>
  </body>
